text: Michael John Randal MacKellar (27 October 1938 - 9 May 2015) was an Australian politician and agricultural scientist. He was the Liberal Member for Warringah from 25 October 1969 until 18 February 1994. MacKellar was born in Moree, New South Wales. He had a partner and had three children. He died at the age of 76. ==References== Category:1938 births Category:2015 deaths Category:Australian scientists Category:Liberal Party of Australia politicians Category:Members of the Australian House of Representatives Category:Order of Australia Category:Politicians from New South Wales
